Other question is whether we care to support the recursive option in the case where group is not specified.  In which case we'd need to check within the nargs == 4 case as to whether we have <owner> <group> <path> or <owner> <path> recursive.  Might be less ambiguous if we prefix the options with a dash (-) or double dash (--) ala conventional short/long options, but still at the end rather than beginning.
chown <owner> [<group>] <path> [--recursive|-R]

